Coffee Maker Teardown — Lab Notes
Date: 2026-03-09
Initially pulled this machine apart assuming it had a pump — intended to scrap it for the pump component. After teardown, discovered it actually operates on a thermosiphon principle (passive water transfer driven by heat and density differential, no mechanical pump).
Decided to repurpose the unit for the lab instead of scrapping it.
Parts Retained

Thermosiphon tube assembly
Thermal fuse (non-resettable, check temp rating)
Thermostat (bimetal, resettable)

Next Steps
Will integrate the thermosiphon assembly into the lab environment as a process control demonstration — see notes on that later.

